    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese porcelain ware that was developed in the 18th century in modern-day Hakoda, within the city of Kasama. Ware includes a household goods, kitchen containers, mixing bowls, and jugs; after WW II, export goods such as tea vessels, flower vases, and sake containers were manufactured.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
